channel.title: Another Question
channel.description:
Well, i'm currently not on my home computer, and the computer i'm on has restrictions.
Like, whenever i make a new folder and try to open it, my access has been denied, or when i try to install java, my access is denied. And i've tried going through safe mode and it wont work.
Anyone know how i can get admin rights, like being able to make accounts, or bypass the restrictions?

item.dc:creator: @ninja_nub ninja nub
item.description:
@ninja_nub wrote:

Log off your comp (not shutdown), hold ctrl+alt+delete then type in user: administrator

You don’t often need password, well it should work.
